{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774643307,"nonce":"/pA24FNnFpZi2Oi/jRM7Z0UPNw8=","message":"Ambiguity clarification for the issue body:\n\nIn the \"Training Protocol\" section, \"No-SISU baseline\" is well-defined (same perturbation distribution but no SISU contextual signal input to the network). However, \"default hyperparameters from default.yml\" should be specified more concretely for reproducibility. Based on the project configuration at the time of writing, the defaults include:\n\n- Architecture: GRU, 180 hidden units\n- Task: center-out delayed reaches, constant length 0.5\n- Perturbation: gusts (n_expected=3, duration_mean=8)\n- Loss: running_cost (constant position error from go cue)\n- nn_output (control cost weight): 1e-5\n- Training: 10000 batches, batch_size=250\n- 5 replicates (default ensemble)\n\nIf any of these defaults change in default.yml before this experiment is run, the comparison conditions may shift. The key variable being manipulated is hps.method (BCS/DAI/PAI-ASF), with perturbation type (curl field vs constant field) as a secondary factor.\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}